Document: GraphFrame
Path: godot/classes/class_graphframe.rst
Summary: Represents a frame within a GraphEdit node, allowing for grouping and organization of other GraphNode elements.

Inherits: Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

GraphFrame is a control node that acts as a container for other GraphNode nodes within a GraphEdit. It provides a visual boundary and can be used to group related nodes together, improving the organization and readability of complex node graphs. GraphFrames can be moved, resized, and collapsed, offering flexibility in managing the layout of your graph editor.
