Path: godot/classes/class_graphframe.rst
Summary: Introduces the GraphFrame node, a specialized GraphElement for organizing other GraphElements within a GraphEdit.
GraphFrame is a special GraphElement that can be used to organize other GraphElements inside a GraphEdit.
---CHUNK---
Document: GraphFrame
Path: godot/classes/class_graphframe.rst
Summary: Describes the GraphFrame class, a special GraphElement that can contain other GraphElements and automatically manages their positioning.
GraphFrame is a special GraphElement to which other GraphElements can be attached. It can be configured to automatically resize to enclose all attached GraphElements. If the frame is moved, all the attached GraphElements inside it will be moved as well.

A GraphFrame is always kept behind the connection layer and other GraphElements inside a GraphEdit.
---CHUNK---
Document: GraphFrame
Path: godot/classes/class_graphframe.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the GraphFrame class in Godot Engine.

Properties:
* autoshrink_enabled (bool): If true, the frame will automatically shrink to fit its content. Default: true.
* autoshrink_margin (int): The margin to apply when autoshrinking. Default: 40.
* drag_margin (int): The margin around the frame that allows dragging. Default: 16.
* mouse_filter (MouseFilter): Controls how mouse events are handled by the control. Default: 0. This property overrides the Control.mouse_filter property.
* tint_color (Color): The color used for tinting the frame. Default: Color(0.3, 0.3, 0.3, 0.75).
* tint_color_enabled (bool): If true, the tint_color will be applied to the frame. Default: false.
* title (String): The title displayed on the frame. Default: "".
---CHUNK---
