Document: GraphFrame
Path: godot/classes/class_graphframe.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring the GraphFrame's appearance and behavior, including autoshrinking, margins, and tinting.

Property: autoshrink_enabled (bool)
Default: true
Setter: set_autoshrink_enabled(value: bool)
Getter: is_autoshrink_enabled()
Description: If true, the frame's rect will be adjusted automatically to enclose all attached GraphElement nodes.

Property: autoshrink_margin (int)
Default: 40
Setter: set_autoshrink_margin(value: int)
Getter: get_autoshrink_margin()
Description: The margin around the attached nodes that is used to calculate the size of the frame when autoshrink_enabled is true.

Property: drag_margin (int)
Default: 16
Setter: set_drag_margin(value: int)
Getter: get_drag_margin()
Description: The margin inside the frame that can be used to drag the frame.

Property: tint_color (Color)
Default: Color(0.3, 0.3, 0.3, 0.75)
Setter: set_tint_color(value: Color)
Getter: get_tint_color()
Description: The color of the frame when tint_color_enabled is true.

Property: tint_color_enabled (bool)
Default: false
Setter: set_tint_color_enabled(value: bool)
Getter: is_tint_color_enabled()
Description: If true, the tint color will be used to tint the frame.

Property: title (String)
Default: ""
Setter: set_title(value: String)
Getter: get_title()
Description: Title of the frame.
